---
layout: layout.njk
title: "Sicily | Fabrizio Vinciguerra"
description: "A personal landscape shaped by volcanic earth, forests, silence and the sea."
---

<section class="collection-hero">
  <img src="/assets/images/sicily.jpg" alt="Sicily">

  <div class="collection-hero-content">
    <p class="subtitle">Collection 03</p>
    <h1>Sicily</h1>
    <p>A land shaped by fire, silence and memory.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="fine-art-story waterfall-story">

  <div class="travel-quote reveal">
    <p>
      Sicily is not a place.<br>
      It is a landscape that never stops changing.
    </p>
  </div>

{% for photo in sicily %}

    {% if loop.index == 4 %}
      <div class="travel-quote reveal">
        <p>
          Fire destroys.<br>
          Nature quietly begins again.
        </p>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if loop.index == 7 %}
      <div class="travel-quote reveal">
        <p>
          Every forest keeps a silence<br>
          different from the previous one.
        </p>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if loop.index == 12 %}
      <div class="travel-quote reveal">
        <p>
          Beyond the volcano,<br>
          the sea remembers everything.
        </p>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <figure class="story-image travel-image {{ photo.class }} reveal">
      <img
        src="{{ photo.src }}"
        alt="{{ photo.alt }}"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        class="lightbox-image"
        data-full="{{ photo.src }}"
        data-title=""
      >
    </figure>

{% endfor %}

<div class="travel-closing reveal">
  <p>
    Some places remain inside you.<br>
    Sicily has always been one of them.
  </p>
</div>

</section>